      "text": "set %a% = \u00220.1\u0022 as number/decimal",
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "Decimal exactness is opt-in: bare literals are double (0.1 \u002B 0.2 \u2192 0.30000\u20264),\nso for exact decimal arithmetic both operands are cast \u0060as number/decimal\u0060. Pins\nthat decimal operands stay decimal and add exactly (0.1 \u002B 0.2 = 0.3).",
